f(x,y) = \frac{1}{8 \pi}\exp(-(x^2+y^2)/8)
P(X_1^2+X_2^2 \le t^2) = \int \int_{B(0,t)} f(x,y) \, dy \, dx 
= \int_0^{2\pi} \int_0^t \frac{1}{8 \pi} \exp(-r^2/8) r \, dr \, d\theta = 1 - \exp(-t^2/8) 
